author: edson.eth
content: Hi, looking through the EIPIP video. Wrt master vs main. Now, if you create a new repo on Github, the default branch will be called main, not master. That said, I don't think it's an important enough issue to change it to main, or gather consensus for this change before changing it

author: edson.eth
content: So to Greg's point, that it's been master for so long, that it may cause confusion. Over time, confusion won't be an issue, as all new repos are being called main for the default branch

author: samwilsn
content:
If you create a repository on GitHub without any content, the default branch is set to whatever you first push to. If you create it with content, then yes, GitHub defaults to `main`.

Git itself, as far as I remember, still defaults to `master`, and prints a warning asking you to set your own default.
